In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. reports on a series of attacks perpetrated by Iranian militia groups affiliated with the Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) against United States personnel and facilities in Iraq and Syria. In response to these attacks and ongoing threats, the President directed targeted strikes against IRGC facilities in eastern Syria. The purpose of these strikes was to establish deterrence, protect and defend US personnel, degrade and disrupt attacks against the US and its partners, and deter further attacks. The President asserts that this military action was taken to fulfill his responsibility to protect US citizens and in accordance with the United States' national security and foreign policy interests. He also states that the action was consistent with international law and the US' right to self-defense. The President concludes by expressing readiness to take further action if necessary and providing this report to Congress in compliance with the War Powers Resolution.